{%- comment -%}
  ================================================================================
  MALLEM RTL WRAPPER
  ================================================================================

  CRITICAL: Shopify-native RTL detection for Arabic/MENA markets

  WHY this snippet exists:
  - Shopify controls lang="{{ request.locale.iso_code }}" (layout/theme.liquid)
  - This snippet adds dir="rtl" for RTL languages
  - CSS logical properties in theme respond to dir attribute
  - NO JavaScript involved - pure Shopify Liquid

  HOW it works:
  1. Shopify user selects language (e.g., العربية)
  2. Shopify POSTs to /localization
  3. Shopify reloads page with request.locale.iso_code = "ar"
  4. This snippet outputs dir="rtl" class="mallem-rtl"
  5. CSS activates RTL styles automatically

  RTL LANGUAGES SUPPORTED:
  - Arabic (ar) - Primary target for mallem theme
  - Hebrew (he)
  - Farsi/Persian (fa)
  - Urdu (ur)

  OUTPUT EXAMPLES:
  - Arabic:  dir="rtl" class="mallem-rtl"
  - English: dir="ltr" class="mallem-ltr"

  USAGE:
  <html lang="{{ request.locale.iso_code }}" {% render 'mallem-rtl-wrapper' %}>

  ================================================================================
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    Extract primary language code from locale
    Example: "ar-SA" becomes "ar", "en-US" becomes "en"
    WHY: Regional variants share same directionality
  endcomment
  assign current_locale = request.locale.iso_code | split: '-' | first | downcase

  comment
    Define RTL language codes (MENA + Middle East languages)
    WHY these four: Cover 99% of RTL e-commerce markets
    - ar (Arabic): Morocco, Egypt, Saudi Arabia, UAE, etc.
    - he (Hebrew): Israel
    - fa (Persian): Iran
    - ur (Urdu): Pakistan
  endcomment
  assign rtl_languages = 'ar,he,fa,ur' | split: ','

  comment
    Check if current locale is RTL
    WHY simple loop: Liquid has no "contains" for arrays
  endcomment
  assign is_rtl = false
  for rtl_lang in rtl_languages
    if current_locale == rtl_lang
      assign is_rtl = true
      break
    endif
  endfor

  comment
    Set direction and CSS class
    WHY separate class: Allows CSS hooks for RTL-specific styling
    Example: .mallem-rtl .product-card { ... }
  endcomment
  if is_rtl
    assign direction = 'rtl'
    assign direction_class = 'mallem-rtl'
  else
    assign direction = 'ltr'
    assign direction_class = 'mallem-ltr'
  endif
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  OUTPUT: HTML attributes for <html> tag
  WHY no line breaks: Clean attribute output in source
{%- endcomment -%}
dir="{{ direction }}" class="{{ direction_class }}"
